thread.title: Grain higher and livestock mixed

title: Grain higher and livestock mixed
text:
Tue, Aug 11, 2015, 6:16 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 3 hrs 44 mins Grain higher and livestock mixed Wheat, corn, oats and soybeans higher on the CBOT; beef higher, pork lower on the CME. Associated Press – 25 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were higher Monday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was up 15 cents to $5.2550 a bushel; December corn gained 17.25 cents to 4.01 a bushel; December oats rose 3.50 cents to 2.4775 a bushel; while November soybeans advanced 31.25 cents to $9.9450 a bushel. 
Beef was higher and pork fell on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was up .78 cent to $1.4930 a pound; August feeder cattle gained .13 cent to $2.1425 a pound; while October lean hogs lost 1.15 cents to $.6297 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Rent rises slowest on record: RP Data AAP
